(1, 'India plans railway circuit to connect with Nepal, Bhutan, BÃ?Â¢??desh and Myanmar', '<p><strong>KATHMANDU</strong>: India plans to link up with four neighbouring countries Ã¢?? Nepal, Bhutan, Bangladesh and Myanmar Ã¢?? through railways and build a railway circuit in the region, according to Indian media that referred to an announcement made by an Indian minister.</p>\r\n<p>Ã¢??We have neighbouring countries like Bangladesh, Bhutan, Myanmar and Nepal. We have a very cordial relationship with them. We want to increase railway connectivity with these countries. We are trying to develop it,Ã¢?? Press Trust of India quoted Indian Railway Minister Suresh Prabhu.</p>\r\n<div class="teads-inread" style="transition-duration: 0.5s; height: 0px;">Ã?Â </div>\r\n<p>Ã¢??If a circuit can be made connecting these neighbouring countries, it will increase interaction, tourism, trade, employment and connectivity,Ã¢?? he added.</p>\r\n<p>The Indian minister revealed his governmentÃ¢??s plan after an agreement between the Indian Railways and UNESCO was signed in Darjeeling on Friday.</p>\r\n<p>Nepal, India, Bangladesh, Bhutan, and Myanmar are members of regional organisation BIMSTEC along with Sri Lanka and Thailand.</p>\r\n<p>Earlier, it bid to build connectivity and increase economic cooperation with its neigbhours, China introduced its ambitious and signature One Belt One Road Initiative in 2013.</p>', 'kathmandu,nepal, bangladesh', 'News', 'assets/images/send.PNG', 'suman', '2017-02-01', 1007, 600, NULL),
(2, 'Saudi Arabian diplomat gets jail time, caning for molesting intern', '<p style="margin: 10px 0px 1.5em; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; text-indent: 0px; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SINGAPORE &mdash; A Saudi Arabian diplomat was on Friday (Feb 3) sentenced to 26 months and a week&rsquo;s jail, and four strokes of the cane for forcefully kissing and groping a hotel trainee while he was on holiday in Singapore.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Bander Yahya A Alzahrani, who is married with three children and based in Beijing, was found guilty of two counts of outrage of modesty and one count of using criminal force on the 20-year-old victim, who cannot be named to protect her identity.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Alzahrani&rsquo;s lawyers have filed a notice to appeal against his conviction and sentence. He is out on S$20,000 bail.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">During the eight-day trial, the court heard that Alzahrani molested the victim twice within 15 minutes, such as by kissing her neck and face, and touching her all over her body. This was while she was showing him around a panoramic suite in Sentosa resort island. Prosecutors said that he also asked her for sex.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Pressing for a sentence of 27.5 months&rsquo; jail and four strokes of the cane, the prosecution emphasised that Alzahrani had not pleaded guilty at the earliest instance. &ldquo;In claiming trial, (he) had forced the victim to recount and relive the trauma (of the incident),&rdquo; Deputy Public Prosecutor Kenny Yang said.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Agreeing, District Judge Lee noted that the victim broke down during her testimony, saying it was &ldquo;painful to remember everything in so (much) detail&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&ldquo;(She) was put through the trauma of recalling and talking about the incident which had been haunting her and she wanted to forget,&rdquo; the judge added.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Pleading for a lighter sentence of 25 months&rsquo; jail, defence lawyer Shashi Nathan told the court that the episode had been &ldquo;deeply, deeply embarrassing&rdquo; for Alzahrani&rsquo;s family members.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Mr Nathan also urged the court to take into consideration that Alzahrani is the sole breadwinner in his family.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">In sentencing him, District Judge Lee commended the resort employees for their alertness and for the &ldquo;many hours (that) were expended&rdquo; in getting information from the victim.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">However, she said: &ldquo;The wisdom of sending a young female intern, alone, to show a room to a male guest is a separate matter.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The Saudi Arabia embassy in Singapore and China did not respond to TODAY&rsquo;s request for comments.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 1.5em 0px; font-family: ''Benton Modern RE'', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: #000000; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Alzahrani could have been jailed up to 10 years, with caning for each charge of outraging the victim&rsquo;s modesty. For using criminal force on her, he could have been jailed up to three months and/or fined up to S$1,500.</p>', '', 'News', 'assets/images/send.PNG', 'ramesh', '2017-01-11', 1018, 599, NULL),
(3, 'Snap''s Story: The Next Big Thing Or A Disappearing Act?', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The <a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #003891;" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/kathleenchaykowski/2017/02/02/snap-with-404-5-million-in-revenue-plans-to-raise-3-billion-in-ipo/#7ef40fc1681f">Snap IPO filing</a>&nbsp;might be best summed up by one of the&nbsp;app''s most famous visual effects: puking rainbows. On the one hand, the visual effect of endless rainbow streams evokes the prodigious revenues and sometimes magical innovation&nbsp;Snap has achieved in its short history. On the other hand, the company''s massive losses, negative gross margins, and slowing user growth could cause investors to throw up in the years to come. And whether Snap''s future is blue skies or the bottom of a toilet might very well rest on its ability to create hits like puking rainbows. Queasy yet?</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">On the plus side, Snap''s revenue growth is astounding.&nbsp;</strong>With $404 million last year, Snap grew sevenfold over 2015. For a 5-year-old company to be closing in on half a billion in revenues and having the 10-figure mark well within its sights is a rare achievement even in the "unicorn" club. When CEO Evan Spiegel was rumored to be focused on monetization in the early days of Snap, critics suggested that kind of thing could wait. "Build the user base first" was the somewhat nonsensical mantra of what was once called the Web 2.0 era. Spiegel, all of 26, is about to <a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #003891;" href="http://www.trippedmedia.com/celebrities/miranda-kerr-wedding-wedding-plans-snapchat-founder/207313/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">marry a supermodel</a> while taking his company public and putting his net worth north of $4 billion. That''s higher than the $3 billion he turned down for&nbsp;<a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #003891;" href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/jjcolao/2014/01/06/the-inside-story-of-snapchat-the-worlds-hottest-app-or-a-3-billion-disappearing-act/#634c19e655ec" target="_self"><em style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: italic; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">all of the company</em></a> just 3 years ago. Game, set, match, Spiegel.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">There''s also a great deal of upside.&nbsp;</strong><a style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #003891;" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/kathleenchaykowski/2017/02/02/this-stat-shows-how-far-snap-has-to-go-to-catch-up-to-facebook/#1165291a3839">Here in&nbsp;FORBES</a>, Kathleen Chaykowski highlighted a major difference between Facebook and Snap: the social networking giant is earning far more per user. But that''s not a negative; it''s opportunity for the much younger company. Facebook has grown average revenue per North American user to $19.81 in the quarter that just ended vs. just $2.15 for Snap. Sounds bad until you realize Facebook has boosted&nbsp;that figure nearly 5x in the past four years. Given the relative newness of Snap''s advertising products and the inherent visual richness of the platform, it isn''t difficult to imagine similar growth. With even more runway overseas it also isn''t hard to imagine Snap growing&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: italic; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">significantly</em> from here just by selling more advertising to existing users.</p>\r\n<div id="article-0-inread" class="inread ng-isolate-scope inread-active" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id="attachment_9120" class="wp-caption alignright" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 9.79688px -19.6094px 9.79688px 19.6094px; padding: 18.2031px 0px; border-width: 3px 0px; border-image: initial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 0; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; width: 280.156px; float: right; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; border-color: #cccccc initial #cccccc initial; border-style: solid initial solid initial;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">But there''s where it starts to get scary.&nbsp;</strong>Something is already broken in Snap''s growth story. In the past 6 months, daily average users have only grown by 15 million users. It was 36 million in the prior 6 months, which shows a dramatic slow down in growth. That might be OK if Snapchat already had hundreds of million of users, but it doesn''t. The year ended with just 161 million, including 68 million in North America. While that too would seem to leave a big opportunity to Snapchat to grow, there are plenty of red flags. First, 85% of users are between 13-34. It''s simply not clear Snapchat is a product that will appeal to as wide a demographic as Facebook or even Twitter. Second, growth outside of North America and Europe has literally stopped for the moment. Third, not everything grows forever -- just ask Twitter.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">It''s good to be clever, but hard to protect innovation.&nbsp;</strong>Snapchat blames part of the growth slowdown on technical problems and there were issues with its Android client last year. But there''s little doubt that an important copycat played a role too: the 900-pound gorilla Facebook. Playful filters now are present in Facebook''s Messenger, which has more than 1 billion users. And Facebook''s Instagram last summer added&nbsp;a Stories feature that mimics Snapchat''s. With 400+ million users, it represents more formidable competition. In Asia, an app called Snow has caught on with Snapchat-like filters and tens of millions of downloads. Clones don''t always hurt, but the numbers here suggest they''re affecting Snap.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; line-height: 1.4em; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; vertical-align: baseline; -webkit-margin-before: 0px; -webkit-margin-after: 0px; -webkit-padding-start: 0px; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Network effects ain''t what they used to be.&nbsp;</strong>This perhaps presents the biggest challenge for Snap. In a world with few social networks the boost&nbsp;from adding users to one increased its value significantly. In a world with lots of networks, users value each of them relatively less even while they belong to many. Facebook was willing to spend billions to acquire both Instagram and WhatsApp because it saw the importance of maintaining&nbsp;leadership in image sharing and chat to orbit around its core social network. Snap has extraordinary popularity with its users but those who don''t use Snap&nbsp;have multiple ways to reach friends who do, even with similar kinds of interaction as filters, stories, and ubiquitous image sharing have proliferated.</p>', 'snap story,kinds', 'News', 'assets/images/post.PNG', 'sudhan', '2017-01-17', 999, 598, NULL),
(4, 'Red Dot Traffic Building to be restored to original off-white colour', '<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SINGAPORE: The Red Dot Traffic Building, known for its eye-catching red hue, will be restored to its original off-white colour as part of a S$25 million restoration plan, the Ministry of Law announced on Friday (Feb 3).</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Built in 1928, the iconic building at 28 Maxwell Street used to house the former Singapore Traffic Police Headquarters, and was given conservation status by the Urban Redevelopment Authority in 2007. It is now home to the Red Dot Design Museum and other tenants.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The building will be taken over by the Law Ministry in May as part of the <a style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; outline: 0px; line-height: inherit; background-color: transparent; color: #665e80; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;" href="http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/maxwell-chambers-to-expand-by-taking-over-red-dot-traffic/3416452.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">expansion of the adjacent Maxwell Chambers</a>. Announced in January, the expansion is aimed at meeting growing demand and bolstering Singapore''s position as an international dispute resolution centre.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The expansion will add a total of 120,000 sqft of space to Maxwell Chambers, tripling its current size. The new building will house about 50 offices for international dispute resolution institutions, arbitration chambers, law firms and ancillary legal services over four floors.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The refurbishment of the building will focus on restoring its heritage, the Law Ministry said.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Architectural elements such as timbre louver windows and cast-iron rainwater downpipes which had been removed or fallen into disrepair will be restored. The five courtyards inside the building will be also be restored to their original open-to-sky design and opened for public use.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Also in the plans are a new link-bridge to connect the building to Maxwell Chambers'' current premises, a new annex block to add 3,230 sqft of office space and a new corridor block.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">A tender for construction will be called in February. Restoration works will start in May and will be completed in 2019.&nbsp;</p>', 'red dot,traffic', 'Blogging,News', 'assets/images/post.PNG', 'shyam', '2017-01-16', 997, 597, NULL),
(5, 'How much did #DeleteUber actually hurt Uber?', '<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/29/delete-uber-social-media-campaign/"><ins>#DeleteUber </ins></a>movement became a major trend over the weekend after President Donald Trump''s travel ban on immigrants from seven Muslim majority countries caused chaos in airports.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="fb-quote fb_iframe_widget" style="display: inline-block; position: absolute; margin-bottom: 2rem; left: 415.5px; top: 753px;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">When Uber <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://twitter.com/Uber_NYC/status/825502908926066688" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">turned off surge pricing</a> shortly after a taxi strike in opposition of the ban (the strike was in effect from 6 to 7 p.m., and the tweet announcing the lift in surge pricing appeared at 7:36 p.m.) it was read as an affront to the protesters and social media rage hit ride-hailing company like a brick. Former Uber devotees <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/30/deleteuber-excuses/">shared screenshots</a> of their reasons for deleting the app in droves &mdash; much to the delight of rival Lyft, which capitalized on the controversy (and a <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/29/lyft-aclu-donation-trump-muslim-ban/">public $1 million pledge</a> to the ACLU) and <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/30/delete-uber-trump-immigration-ads/">overtook Uber</a> in total App Store downloads for the first time ever on Sunday.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/31/uber-needed-new-account-deletion-process/">Uber even acknowledged</a> difficulties deleting user accounts as public sentiment appeared to have turned against the ride-hailing giant (the app didn''t have an automatic client to handle account cancellations until Monday night).</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">But how effective was the #DeleteUber movement, really? It got Uber CEO Travis Kalanick <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/02/02/delete-uber-travis-kalanick-resign-trump/">to step down from Trump''s advisory economic council</a>, but did everyone actually follow through on their online anger and stop using the app? Or was last weekend just a blip on Uber''s radar, yet another moment of viral anger to be forgotten?</p>\r\n<div class="see-also" style="font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<p class="see-also-link" style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; display: block;">SEE ALSO: <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none; text-transform: none;" href="http://mashable.com/2017/01/28/tim-cook-apple-uber-trump-immigration-ban/">Apple, Uber, Netflix, Twitter join corporate rebuke of Trump immigration policy</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">More than 200,000 people said bye-bye to their Uber accounts, according to the <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/02/technology/uber-ceo-travis-kalanick-trump-advisory-council.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em style="font-style: italic;">New York Times</em></a>. But that''s a small fraction of the company''s monthly active users: <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="http://fortune.com/2016/10/20/uber-app-riders/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">40 million as of October.</a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">But the hashtag was still shrouding Uber in negativity, even if only a small percentage actually deleted their accounts. To further investigate the extent of the impact, we looked at web traffic numbers and app installation data from both Uber and Lyft. It''s important to note that we compare different stats across multiple platforms, so the analysis won''t be a full picture &mdash; but we <em style="font-style: italic;">can</em> get a good idea of what happened outside of the social media echo chamber.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Let''s break it down by platform.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style="margin: 0px 0px 1rem; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color: #555555; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.27; clear: left; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Web traffic</h2>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.similarweb.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SimilarWeb</a>, a digital market intelligence company, pulled the numbers for Jan. 4 through Jan. 28 for Uber''s online HQ, <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://www.uber.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">uber.com</a>. This data was for the period as a whole, so the impact of the #DeleteUber weekend isn''t obvious at first glance, but by comparing the numbers to those of December 2016, we can see some dramatic changes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SimilarWeb found the term "delete uber account" was the 12th most popular source for driving traffic. To put that in perspective, the term was the 177th most popular in December 2016.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Among uber.com&rsquo;s pages, the support portal for <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://help.uber.com/h/24010fe7-7a67-4ee5-9938-c734000b144a" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">deleting the app</a> did show a substantial increase in visits compared to the month before. The page was the 14th most visited on the site. In December 2016, it was ranked 82nd.</p>\r\n<h2 style="margin: 0px 0px 1rem; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color: #555555; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.27; clear: left; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">iOS</h2>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">To track App Store stats, we reached out to <a style="color: #00aeef; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sensortower.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SensorTower</a>, a mobile data insights provider. They provided us with estimates of the daily download numbers for both the Uber and Lyft apps for the last week of January and the first few days of February.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">After things died down in the first few days of February, however, the ranking stats show Uber back on top, with only a slight dip in ranking as Lyft''s momentum falls away. Importantly, no re-downloads or uninstalls are reflected in these figures, so it''s unclear how many repentant Uber users contributed to the data.</p>\r\n<div class="fb-quote fb_iframe_widget" style="display: inline-block; position: absolute; margin-bottom: 2rem; left: 442.5px; top: 3020px;"><span style="display: inline-block; position: relative; text-align: justify; vertical-align: bottom; width: 169px; height: 47px;"><iframe class="" style="border: none; position: absolute; visibility: visible; width: 169px; height: 47px;" title="fb:quote Facebook Social Plugin" src="https://www.facebook.com/v2.5/plugins/quote.php?app_id=122071082108&amp;channel=http%3A%2F%2Fstaticxx.facebook.com%2Fconnect%2Fxd_arbiter%2Fr%2FSh-3BhStODe.js%3Fversion%3D42%23cb%3Dfeccb13fe8546c%26domain%3Dmashable.com%26origin%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fmashable.com%252Ffc992955cef34c%26relation%3Dparent.parent&amp;container_width=943&amp;href=http%3A%2F%2Fmashable.com%2F2017%2F02%2F02%2Freal-effect-of-delete-uber%2F%23dh2SJBp9vmqJ&amp;locale=en_US&amp;sdk=joey" name="f268c4e0003c6ec" width="1000px" height="1000px" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></span></div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The iOS data shows that #DeleteUber made a quick impact &mdash; but the damage it caused was fleeting.</p>\r\n<h2 style="margin: 0px 0px 1rem; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color: #555555; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.27; clear: left; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Android</h2>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SimilarWeb''s report claims there was a spike in the total downloads metric for Lyft on Jan. 28 (the start of the movement), suggesting #DeleteUber may have had some impact. Still, the firm determined the influx was not significant enough to influence the general trend.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">In addition, their data shows there was no significant change to install percentages (which the firm defines as current installations of the app as a percentage of all Android devices in the U.S.) on Android devices for Uber or Lyft from Jan. 4 to Jan. 31.</p>\r\n<h2 style="margin: 0px 0px 1rem; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color: #555555; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.27; clear: left; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Real impact</h2>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">While the data shows us #DeleteUber didn''t have a significant effect on the app ecosystem, it isn''t a true barometer.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0.75em 0px 1.5em; color: #555555; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The real impact of hashtags like #DeleteUber is corporate action &mdash; which is exactly what we saw with Kalanick''s resignation from Trump''s advisory council. &nbsp;</p>', 'uber', 'How Tos', 'assets/images/uber.PNG', 'sudhan', '2017-01-08', 997, 598, NULL);
