(6, 'Wistron plant in Indian tech hub solely for iPhone: source', '<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">MUMBAI/TAIPEI: An assembly plant that Apple''s Taiwanese manufacturing partner Wistron Corp is setting up in Bengaluru will focus solely on assembling iPhones, a source familiar with the matter said on Friday.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The source, who asked not to be named because he was not cleared to discuss matters publicly, said Apple and the Indian government were, however, still discussing "the repatriation of long-term profits from local sales and exports."</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The government of the Indian state of Karnataka said on Thursday it welcomed Apple''s proposal to begin initial manufacturing operations in tech hub Bengaluru, its state capital, hinting it is moving forward with plans to assemble iPhones in India.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"Apple''s intentions to manufacture in Bengaluru will foster a cutting edge technology ecosystem and supply chain development in the state, which are critical for India to compete globally," the Karnataka government said in a statement.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Karnataka IT Minister Priyank Kharge told Reuters on Friday he believes Apple will "tentatively begin manufacturing iPhones in the state by the end of April, or beginning of May."</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">A second source familiar with matters told Reuters, however, that no agreement, or memorandum of understanding has so far been finalised with the Karnataka government.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The person, who also asked not to be named, said if Apple did go ahead with plans to begin assembling the iPhone, it was likely to do so initially at the plant being set up by Wistron at Peenya on the outskirts of Bengaluru.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Apple was not immediately reachable for comment.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Joyce Chou, a spokeswoman for Wistron, said its Bengaluru plant is expected to begin producing smartphones some time in the first half of 2017. She declined to comment on whether it would be a captive iPhone assembly site.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Cupertino, California-based Apple, is keen to assemble its phones in India, one of the world''s fastest growing smartphone markets.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Apple representatives met federal and state government officials in India last week, as it is lobbies hard for tax and sourcing concessions before it begins to assemble iPhones there.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Apple described its discussions with Indian officials as open and constructive.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Any final decision on manufacturing in India is, however, likely to depend on the government''s willingness to concede ground on the concessions Apple seeks.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Last month, Information Technology Minister Ravi Shankar Prasad said India would consider Apple''s request for incentives with an "open mind."</p>', 'messaging', 'Blogging,News', 'assets/images/wilstron.PNG', 'suman', '2017-01-01', 994, 1000, NULL),
(7, 'Popular messaging app Line ', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">SINGAPORE - From today till April 2, fans of messaging app Line can go to a Line Friends pop-up "store" at Westgate located inside Samsung''s Experience Store.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Line''s multi-platform messaging app - launched in 2011 - offers free voice calls and group chats. It is known for its original and cute virtual sticker characters like Brown, Cony and Sally, called Line Friends.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The pop-up store on the third floor will not be selling Line Friends merchandise, as it is a special collaboration between Samsung and Line. Instead, it will sell Samsung smartphones like the Galaxy A5 (2017) and A7 (2017) smartphones bundled with a Line power bank (worth $108).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="ads clearleft" style="box-sizing: border-box; clear: left !important; background-color: #ffffff; text-align: center; padding: 30px 0px 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The pop-up also allows users to explore new ways to customise their Samsung devices with Line merchandise, while getting up-close with their favourite Line characters in five experiential zones.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Visitors can take a 360-degree selfie using Samsung Gear 360 camera with their favourite Line characters, or enjoy a virtual reality roller-coaster ride with Brown and Sally using Samsung Gear VR.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="innity-in-post" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">All visitors can redeem complimentary Line merchandise when they take part in any three of the experiential zones.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The Samsung x Line Friends pop-up store opening hours are: 11am to 10pm (daily); except for today (opened from 6pm) and Feb 11 (when it will be closed from 11am to 4pm).</p>', 'messaging', 'Mobile', 'assets/images/messaging.PNG', 'ramesh', '2017-01-10', 800, 999, NULL),
(8, 'Trump says ''tough phone calls'' needed', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 17px; letter-spacing: 0.17px; line-height: 30px; margin: 0px auto 30px; max-width: 730px; padding: 0px 55px; width: 730px; font-family: Larsseit, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">WASHINGTON, Feb 2 (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump told a national prayer breakfast on Thursday that the world is in trouble, the United States is being taken advantage of, and that he was having "tough phone calls" as he worked to address issues.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 17px; letter-spacing: 0.17px; line-height: 30px; margin: 0px auto 30px; max-width: 730px; padding: 0px 55px; width: 730px; font-family: Larsseit, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">"The world is in trouble, but we''re going to straighten it out, OK? That''s what I do - I fix things," Trump said after saying that freedom of religion was threatened.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 17px; letter-spacing: 0.17px; line-height: 30px; margin: 0px auto 30px; max-width: 730px; padding: 0px 55px; width: 730px; font-family: Larsseit, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">"Believe me, when you hear about the tough phone calls I''m having - don''t worry about it. Just don''t worry about it," he said.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-size: 17px; letter-spacing: 0.17px; line-height: 30px; margin: 0px auto 30px; max-width: 730px; padding: 0px 55px; width: 730px; font-family: Larsseit, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">"We''re taken advantage of by every nation in the world virtually. It''s not going to happen anymore," he said. (Reporting by Roberta Rampton; Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)</p>', 'washington,trump,donald', 'Blogging,News', 'assets/images/trump.PNG', 'sudhan', '2017-01-18', 700, 998, NULL),
(9, 'What is IoT?', '<h2 class="short-teaser" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: italic; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.2; font-family: ''Droid Sans Bold''; font-size: 1.2em; vertical-align: baseline; width: 510px; box-sizing: border-box; float: right; color: #333333; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Wondering about the Internet of Things? Here''s our guide to the IoT</h2>\r\n<div class="field field-name-body" style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Droid Sans''; font-size: 17.6px; vertical-align: baseline; width: 510px; box-sizing: border-box; float: right; color: #333333; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Droid Sans Bold''; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline;">What is IoT?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">If <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.itpro.co.uk/tags/ces-2017">CES</a>&nbsp;in January told us anything, it&rsquo;s that 2017 will be the year of the Internet of Things (IoT), but what exactly is this new term that we will be hearing so much about?</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">Simply put, IoT is the connection of devices to the internet, where they are able to communicate with each other and their users. This can be something simple, such as a smartphone synced with a television, to more complex networks monitoring urban infrastructure and traffic. Today this includes washing machines, fridges, wearables, walking sticks &ndash; pretty much any device you can think of.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">But the undisputed king of the IoT device has to be the <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.itpro.co.uk/desktop-hardware/26577/google-home-vs-amazon-echo-vs-apple-home-alexa-adds-ifttt-support">smart-home assistant</a>, which has seen a surge in popularity over the last year. Amazon Echo, Google Home, Lenovo Smart Assistant, the <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-38074089">DingDong from LingLong</a>&hellip; once one appeared it seemed everyone was jumping on the smart home bandwagon.</p>\r\n<div id="dfp-ad-nativeslot2-wrapper" class="dfp-tag-wrapper" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 17.6px; vertical-align: baseline;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Droid Sans Bold''; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline;">Why is IoT so important?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">It&rsquo;s inevitable that with the growing availability of fast and reliable broadband, devices will increasingly come with WiFi capabilities as standard. The IoT has already allowed devices to assist our daily routines; cars can sync with calendars to track appointments and plan the best routes, and smart assistants have turned online shopping into a simple conversation.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">The most compelling application of the IoT is within society and industry, where machine learning and AI are revolutionising the way we do business. <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.itpro.co.uk/strategy/26561/london-and-bristol-take-smart-cities-crown">Smart cities</a> are enabling us to cut down on waste and energy consumption, while industry has benefited from the connectivity of machines and tracking of its workforce. Even farming is now making use of connected sensors to monitor crops and cattle, to better predict yields and boost efficiency.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Droid Sans Bold''; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline;">Is IoT safe?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">The short answer is <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.itpro.co.uk/security/25970/security-is-the-biggest-barrier-to-iot-adoption">no, not quite yet</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">Connected devices run the risk of creating a security nightmare. Some devices rely on large bandwidths for the transfer of video, such as connected security cameras, and this has drawn the attention of cyber-criminals. Compromised IoT networks have singlehandedly fueled some of the largest DDoS attacks in history, knocking websites and services offline around the world.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">Business customers tend to be savvier about protecting data, but for consumers security is often sidelined in favour of flashy features. Internet security in the home has yet to catch up with the pace of IoT &ndash; <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15.4px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: none; color: #0064af;" href="http://www.itpro.co.uk/routers/27776/netgear-customers-warned-to-stop-using-flawed-routers">standard routers are simply too easy to crack</a> and provide little indication that a device may be compromised.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Droid Sans Bold''; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline;">What lies ahead for IoT?</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.56; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.875em; vertical-align: baseline;">The possibilities for IoT are endless, but it will be some time yet before we truly understand its affect on our lives and the economy. For it to really take off, we need the rest of the technology industry to catch up. Management tools, bespoke IoT operating systems, and communication standards all still need to be properly developed. Right now, we are still in the process of figuring out how best to use the technology. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'Internet of Things', 'News', 'assets/images/IoT.PNG', 'shyam', '2017-01-19', 756, 980, NULL),
(10, 'New Ford Kuga 2017 review', '<h2 class="short-teaser" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 16px; font-family: RobotoItalic; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">We hit British roads to see whether a refresh has brought the Ford Kuga SUV back into contention</h2>\r\n<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.62px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">\r\n<div class="field-items" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<div class="field-item even" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The problem with selling a car in a popular market segment is that you can struggle to get noticed. The <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/ford/kuga">Ford Kuga</a>, for example, only had a handful of competitors when the first-generation model rolled off the line in 2008. But fast forward nine years, and virtually every mainstream car maker has a profitable mid-size <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/best-cars/62060/best-4x4s-and-suvs-2017">SUV</a> ready to poach <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/ford">Ford</a>&rsquo;s sizeable market share.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">&bull;&nbsp;<a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/best-cars/63353/best-crossver-cars-and-small-suvs-on-sale-2016">Best crossovers on sale right now</a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Our favourite SUVs in this class, such as the slightly smaller <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/seat/ateca">SEAT Ateca</a>&nbsp;and <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/peugeot/3008/97317/new-peugeot-3008-2016-review">Peugeot 3008</a>, have pushed the Kuga down the pecking order. Even the outgoing <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/mazda/cx-5">Mazda CX-5</a> could show the Ford a fresh set of heels, with its punchy diesel engine.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">But a facelift can really make a difference &ndash; which is why the company has given the Kuga a similar front grille to the bigger <a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #026ac3; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/ford/edge">Edge</a>, plus restyled lights front and rear, and a reshaped tailgate. The nip and tuck freshens up the design, although we still don&rsquo;t think it&rsquo;s as imposing or attractive as its funkier and more youthful rivals.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Inside, the changes are more limited. Ford has thrown out the low-res screen and mass of fiddly buttons for the old infotainment system and fitted its latest SYNC 3 set-up. It&rsquo;s largely intuitive to operate and only occasionally does it fail to respond to your inputs. It&rsquo;s just a bit odd that the company has recessed the screen into the dash rather than bringing it out at an angle, because this makes the large menu buttons tricky to reach on the move.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Cabin quality is a mixed bag, too. There&rsquo;s a decent amount of soft-touch materials on the dashboard and doors, plus Ford&rsquo;s trademark squidgy steering wheel. But the revised centre console, which houses the new electronic parking brake, features hard and flimsy-feeling glossy plastic.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Ford hasn&rsquo;t just focused on the bits you can see, however. There&rsquo;s a couple of new engines (although the 2.0 TDCi in our car is unchanged), while new torque vectoring technology has been introduced in a bid to boost traction and stability. The suspension is unchanged, however.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, ''Bitstream Vera Sans'', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Like most torque vectoring systems on mainstream cars, you&rsquo;ll only notice the effect if you drive the new model back-to-back with the old one, but either way, it&rsquo;s clear the Kuga is still one of the class&rsquo;s better drivers&rsquo; cars. Body control is pretty good for a small SUV, while the controls are well weighted.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'reviews', 'Make money online', 'assets/images/review.PNG', 'suman', '2017-01-30', 677, 987, NULL);
