(11, 'Samsung Pay Mini Heading To Android Devices This Quarter', '<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Samsung is gearing up to expand its mobile payments platform and will be launching Samsung Pay Mini, the stripped down version of Samsung Pay, in home country South Korea in Q1 2017.</span></p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The mobile payment system, however, will not be exclusive to Samsung Galaxy devices alone and will be compatible with all Android smartphones.</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The <a style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: none; color: #29aba5;" href="https://news.samsung.com/kr/%EC%82%BC%EC%84%B1%EC%A0%84%EC%9E%90-%EC%82%BC%EC%84%B1-%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4-%EB%AF%B8%EB%8B%88-%EC%84%A0%EB%B3%B4%EC%97%AC">announcement</a> confirms that anyone who has a compatible Android smartphone, will be able to deploy Samsung Pay Mini. The app focuses on mobile-based shopping rather than payments. The good news is that the app is compatible with devices that have an HD screen, as well as run on the older Android Lollipop.</p>\n<h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box;">Samsung Pay Mini Release</strong></h3>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Samsung will reportedly have a pre-event on Feb. 6 before it officially launches the app on home ground. Reportedly, any user who has a Samsung Card is eligible to download the Pay Mini app''s trial version from the Google Play Store.</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">However, the Samsung Pay Mini app will be exclusive to South Korea at launch, which means that consumers in the U.S. will not be able to peruse it as of now.</p>\n<h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box;">How Is Samsung Pay Mini Different From Samsung Pay?</strong></h3>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Samsung Pay Mini, however, will not support offline payments unlike <a style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration: none; color: #29aba5;" href="http://www.techtimes.com/articles/185827/20161115/samsung-pay-rewards-program-brings-unprecedented-incentives-for-a-digital-wallet-heres-how-it-works.htm">Samsung Pay</a>. The new app has been designed only so that it can offer support for online payments.</p>\n<p>DiscoverAndroid LollipopMobile paymentSmartphoneSamsung Galaxy</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The mobile payment service is intended for online stores specifically and will offer support for lifestyle, store memberships, as well as transportation. Some online stores affiliated with the service will also offer a rewards program. The more a user shops using Samsung Pay Mini in South Korea - for now - the more rewards they will be able to earn.</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Samsung Pay Mini focuses on online payments and looks to offer a dedicated solution for the platform.</p>\n<div id="kskdk_1cf5a621d260c0386c7dbbeced1711ef" class="kskdDiv kskdCls" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: content-box; display: block; float: none; opacity: 1; position: relative; overflow: visible; width: auto; left: auto; right: auto; transition: none; letter-spacing: normal; white-space: normal; top: auto; bottom: auto; height: auto; min-height: 0px; max-height: non