ns: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Previous reports have suggested that the Samsung Pay Mini app will offer users an easy solution for storing their credit and debit card details, which will expedite the payment process.</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-align: justify;">To make transactions more convenient, the Samsung Pay Mini app was said to store the receipts so that users know what they have purchased. However, Samsung Korea''s announcement does not detail if this feature is included. Moreover, the app was said to deploy fingerprint authentication, as well as a six-character password for enhanced security. Whether Samsung Pay Mini deploys this security feature is also not known.</p>\n<div id="article_body_inread_computer_oop5" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">&nbsp;</div>\n<h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; color: #000000; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box;">U.S. Release</strong></h3>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Samsung has not shed light on when the Samsung Pay Mini app will make its way to Android users in the U.S. However, the company is expected to bring the new service to other markets as well.</p>\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; list-style: none; box-sizing: border-box; font-size: medium; line-height: 1.4em; color: #444444; font-family: Hind, Arial, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Samsung Pay Mini is expected to boost the company''s service offerings portfolio, whether users will take a shine to the same remains to be seen.</p>', 'samsung', 'Gadgets', 'assets/images/samsung.PNG', 'madhusudhan', '2017-01-23', 784, 965, NULL),
(12, 'FCC''s Pai Proposes ATSC 3.0 Rollout', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #302d2d; font-family: Roboto, ''Hevletica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">New <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/articles-taging/fcc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FCC</a> chairman <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/articles-taging/ajit-pai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ajit Pai</a> signaled&nbsp;Thursday that he wants broadcasters to be able to start working on&nbsp;tomorrow''s&nbsp;TV today.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #302d2d; font-family: Roboto, ''Hevletica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Pai, who has only been in the job since Jan. 20, wasted no time prioritizing that goal. He has already circulated a <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/sites/default/files/public/2017/02/Public%20Circulation%20Next%20Gen%20TV%20Document.pdf">Notice of Proposed Rulemaking</a> to the other commissioners that would allow TV stations to start rolling out the <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/news/local-tv/atsc-30-cooler-look-next-gen-standard/161066" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ATSC 3.0 advanced TV transmission standard</a>&nbsp;on a voluntary basis. He hopes to issue final authorization for the new standard by the end of the year, he <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/blog/bc-guest-blogs/guest-blog-fast-forwarding-future-broadcasting/163022" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">said in an op ed in <em style="box-sizing: border-box;">B&amp;C</em></a> explaining the importance of the initiative.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #302d2d; font-family: Roboto, ''Hevletica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"Next Gen TV matters because it will let broadcasters offer much better services in a variety of ways," Pai wrote. "Picture quality will improve with 4K transmissions. Accurate sound localization and customizable sound mixes will produce an immersive audio experience. Broadcasters will be able to provide advanced emergency alerts with more information, more tailored to a viewer&rsquo;s particular location. Enhanced personalization and interactivity will enable better audience measurement, which in turn will make for higher-quality advertising&mdash;ads relevant to you and that you actually might want to see. Perhaps most significantly, consumers will easily be able to watch over-the-air programming on mobile devices."</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #302d2d; font-family: Roboto, ''Hevletica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;"><a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/news/washington/nab-fires-back-atva-atsc-30/161695" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Related: NAB Fires Back at ATVA on ATSC 3.0</a></p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; color: #302d2d; font-family: Roboto, ''Hevletica Neue'', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">According to an FCC official speaking on background, the NPRM is responsive to the <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #3f85d4; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.broadcastingcable.com/news/washington/broadcasters-petition-fcc-atsc-30-rollout/155504" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">petition filed last April</a> by the National Association of Broadcasters (NAB), Consumer Technology Association (CTA), America''s Public Television Stations (APTS) and the Advanced Warning and Response Network (AWARN) Alliance&nbsp;but also incorporates stakeholder input on that petition.</p>', 'FCC', 'Make money online', 'assets/images/fcc.PNG', 'ranjana', '2017-01-24', 879, 90, NULL),
(13, '2017 MINI Cooper Countryman: the little car goes premium', '<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><em><span class="caps">OXFORD</span>, U.K.</em>&mdash;It&rsquo;s the <span class="caps">MINI</span> for people who like the Cooper&rsquo;s style and attitude, but who really want a bigger compact car. The Countryman was the largest <span class="caps">MINI</span> when it was introduced 11 years ago, until it was overtaken in size a couple of years ago by the Clubman.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Now, its second generation is 19 cm longer; three cm wider; and has 30 percent more cargo space than before. It&rsquo;s been updated with the new three- and four-cylinder turbocharged engines found across the rest of the line, and comes with new technology, both optional and standard. But is it still a <span class="caps">MINI</span>?</p>\r\n<h3 id="subnav-section-Walkaround" class="section-block js-section-block" style="margin: 25px 0px 20px; line-height: 1.1em; font-weight: normal; font-family: DINWeb-Light; font-size: 18px; color: #696e74; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Walkaround</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The Countryman stands out in a sea of <span class="caps">MINI</span>s at the assembly plant in Oxford (though it is, in fact, made in The Netherlands) because it&rsquo;s 14 cm taller than the regular three- and five-door Coopers. It&rsquo;s no taller than the previous generation, however. The greater size comes from its all-new architecture, shared with the <span class="caps">BMW</span> X1 compact <span class="caps">SUV</span>, which is itself a little bigger still.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The shape is undoubtedly <span class="caps">MINI</span>, but the new generation is more &ldquo;pared-back and modern&rdquo; according to its designers, which means some of the rounded edges have been squared off, and some extra metal edging added to the wheel arches and surrounding black accent strip.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">The headlights are now each completely surrounded by daytime driving light rings, which is both distinctive and useful. It&rsquo;s the sort of thing you probably wouldn&rsquo;t notice without the two generations sitting side by side, but the end product does look tidy and capable.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-indent: 0px; line-height: 19px; color: #56595e; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Being taller than a &ldquo;regular&rdquo; <span class="caps">MINI</span>, it&rsquo;s easier to get in and out of the Countryman&mdash;passengers sit a little higher and everyone can see a bit farther down the road. This is one of the appeals of an <span class="caps">SUV</span>, and it&rsquo;s quite intentional.</p>', 'mini cooper', 'Blogging', 'assets/images/mini cooper.PNG', 'srijana', '2017-01-26', 67, 789, NULL),
(14, 'GitHub rallies Silicon Valley companies to oppose Muslim ban', '<div class="o-article_block pb-15 pb-5@m- o-subtle_divider" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 35px 0px 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; position: relative; color: #2b2d32; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="grid@tl+" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0px -40px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 0px; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="grid@tl+__cell col-8-of-12@tl+" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: inline-block; vertical-align: top; width: 680px; font-size: medium; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="article-text c-gray-1" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 5px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #2b2d32; font-size: 18px; display: block; line-height: 30px; font-weight: 400; font-family: ''Guardian TextEgyp'', serif !important; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<p style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 15px 0px 5px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: block; font-size: 18px; line-height: 30px; font-weight: 400; font-family: ''Guardian TextEgyp'', serif !important; border: 0px inherit inherit;">GitHub <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-immigration-tech-idUSKBN15F08H">plans to meet</a> with a number of Silicon Valley tech companies to discuss filing an amicus brief in lawsuits targeting Trump''s immigration and refugee ban.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="js-notMobileReferredByFbTw" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #2b2d32; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="o-article_block pb-15 pb-5@m- mt-n35 mt-n25@m mt-n15@s" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: -35px 0px 0px; padding: 35px 0px 15px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="grid@tl+" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0px -40px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-size: 0px; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="full-width@tp- grid@tl+__cell col-8-of-12@tl+" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: inline-block; vertical-align: top; width: 680px; font-size: medium; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<div class="article-text c-gray-1 no-review" style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 5px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #2b2d32; font-size: 18px; display: block; line-height: 30px; font-weight: 400; font-family: ''Guardian TextEgyp'', serif !important; border: 0px inherit inherit;">\r\n<p style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 15px 0px 5px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: block; font-size: 18px; line-height: 30px; font-weight: 400; font-family: ''Guardian TextEgyp'', serif !important; border: 0px inherit inherit;">Those invited, according to a <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-immigration-tech-idUSKBN15F08H"><em style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; border: 0px inherit inherit;">Reuters</em> report</a>, include Google, Netflix and Airbnb. All four of the companies declined to comment on the meeting. Kickstarter, Box, AdRoll and Twilio have voiced their interest in participating as well. Amicus ("friend of the court") briefs are legal documents made by parties not directly involved in a litigation but have a strong interest in the matter. Last year, for example, the tech industry rallied behind <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016/08/04/apple-design-patent-amicus-brief/">Apple in its lawsuit against Samsung</a> and stridently opposed <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/human-rights-campaign-hb2_us_5733a0f0e4b08f96c18218fe">North Carolina''s inhumane HB2 legislation</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 35px 0px 25px; padding: 15px 0px 5px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: block; font-size: 18px; line-height: 30px; font-weight: 400; font-family: ''Guardian TextEgyp'', serif !important; border: 0px inherit inherit;">The group hasn''t specified in which cases the document could or would be filed. If it were to file such a brief, it would place the industry squarely in opposition of the administration. While Silicon Valley has made overtures to Trump''s team during the transition -- going so far as to sit through the president''s theatrics <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="https://www.engadget.com/2016/12/06/trump-team-wants-to-meet-with-silicon-valley-execs-next-week/">during a meeting at Trump Tower</a> in December -- the industry has increasingly objected to his actions through the first two weeks of the presidency. Amazon, Microsoft and Expedia have voiced their support for <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="http://www.atg.wa.gov/news/news-releases/ag-ferguson-seeks-halt-trump-s-immigration-executive-order">Washington State''s lawsuit</a> against Trump''s administration. Google employees <a style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-style: inherit; border-image: initial; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-color: inherit inherit currentcolor inherit;" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017/01/30/googlers-stage-a-walkout-to-protest-trumps-immigration-ban/">staged a work stoppage and protest</a> on Monday.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'git hub', 'News', 'assets/images/git hub.PNG', 'sangita', '2017-01-31', 68, 999, NULL);
