(19, 'Iran vows ''roaring missiles'' if threatened, defies new sanctions', '<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">DUBAI: A Revolutionary Guards commander said Iran would use its missiles if its security is under threat, as the elite force defied new U.S. sanctions on its missile programme by holding a military exercise on Saturday.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Tensions between Tehran and Washington have risen since a recent Iranian ballistic missile test which prompted U.S. President Donald Trump''s administration to impose sanctions on individuals and entities linked to the Revolutionary Guards.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Trump''s national security adviser Michael Flynn said the Washington was putting Iran on notice over its "destabilising activity", and Trump tweeted Tehran was "playing with fire"</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"We are working day and night to protect Iran&rsquo;s security," head of Revolutionary Guards'' aerospace unit, Brigadier General Amir Ali Hajizadeh was quoted as saying by Tasnim news agency.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"If we see smallest misstep from the enemies, our roaring missiles will fall on their heads," he added.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Despite the heated words, U.S. Defense Secretary Jim Mattis said on Saturday he was not considering raising the number of U.S. forces in the Middle East to address Iran''s "misbehaviour", but warned that the world would not ignore Iranian activities.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Iran''s Revolutionary Guards is holding the military exercise in Semnan province on Saturday to test missile and radar systems and to "showcase the power of Iran''s revolution and to dismiss the sanctions," according to the force''s website.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Dismissing Trump''s comments that "nothing is off the table" in dealing with Tehran, the commander of Iran''s ground forces said on Saturday that the Islamic Republic has been hearing such threats since its 1979 revolution.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"The defence capability and the offensive prowess of Iran''s armed forces would make America or any other enemy regretful of any incursion," Ahmad Reza Pourdastan was quoted as saying by ISNA.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">BALLISTIC TEST</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Iranian state news agencies reported that home-made missile systems, radars, command and control centres, and cyber warfare systems would be tested in Saturday''s drill.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Iran has one of the Middle East''s largest missile programmes and held a similar exercise in December to showcase its defence systems, including radars, anti-missile defence units, and short and medium-range missiles.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Tehran confirmed on Wednesday that it had test-fired a new ballistic missile, but said the test did not breach the Islamic Republic''s nuclear agreement with world powers or a U.N. Security Council resolution endorsing the pact.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Iran has test-fired several ballistic missiles since the nuclear deal in 2015, but the latest test was the first since Trump entered the White House. Trump said during his election campaign that he would stop Iran''s missile programme.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The United Nations Security Council held an emergency meeting on Tuesday and recommended the missile testing be studied at committee level. The new U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, Nikki Haley, called the test "unacceptable".</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The Security Council resolution was adopted to buttress the deal under which Iran curbed its nuclear activities to allay concerns they could be used to develop atomic bombs, in exchange for relief from economic sanctions.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The resolution urged Tehran to refrain from work on ballistic missiles designed to deliver nuclear weapons. Critics say the resolution''s language does not make this obligatory.</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; box-sizing: inherit; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0px auto 1rem; padding: 0px 0.9375rem; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; color: #333333; width: 616.656px; max-width: 75rem; float: none; font-family: ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Tehran says it has not carried out any work on missiles specifically designed to carry nuclear payloads.</p>', 'iran', 'Blogging,News', 'assets/images/img.jpg', 'sangita', '2016-12-14', 396, 487, NULL),
(20, 'Pagasa: Bising unlikely to make landfall', '<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">TROPICAL Depression &ldquo;Bising&rdquo; has a little chance of making landfall in the Philippines, according to Romeo Aguirre, weather specialist of Philippine Atmospheric Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (Pagasa) Mactan.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Aguirre said that Cebu will be cloudy today but less chance of rain.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">&ldquo;Bising has also recurved because of the high pressure area coming from China,&rdquo; Aguirre told Cebu Daily News.</p>\r\n<aside style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">\r\n<div id="bb" style="margin: 0px 0px 20px 30px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: 300px; height: auto; float: right; overflow: hidden; position: relative;">\r\n<div id="bbadwrap" class="mrec-art" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: 300px; height: 250px; text-align: center; position: relative;">\r\n<div id="div-gpt-ad-538759236422264763-2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" data-google-query-id="CP7b44Tl9tECFU2maAodkxsLwQ">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id="abdf" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id="abde" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</aside>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">As of 6 p.m. yesterday, Bising was spotted 450 kilometers east of Hinatuan, Surigao del Sur, with a maximum sustained winds of 45 kilometers per hour (kph) and gustiness of up to 55 kph.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Gale warning was issued in Catandunes, eastern coast of Albay, eastern coast of Sorsogon, coast of Northern and Eastern Samar, Surigao, Dinagat Island and Siargao due to Bising.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;">Bising is the second tropical cyclone that entered the Philippine Area of Responsibility (PAR) this 2017 after Auring in January.</p>', 'pagasa', 'News', 'assets/images/pagasa.PNG', 'sroj', '2017-01-25', 516, 873, NULL),
(21, 'Louvre reopens 24 hours after machete attack', '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">PARIS (AFP) - Art lovers returned to the Louvre in Paris on Saturday (Feb 4), 24 hours after a soldier shot a machete-wielding attacker at the museum, believed to be an Egyptian who entered the country a week ago.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The incident on Friday thrust security and the terror threat back into the limelight three months before elections in France, with authorities saying it was a "terrorist" assault.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">It also risked dealing another blow to Paris'' lucrative tourism industry which has been badly affected by a string of attacks since 2015.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">At the Louvre on Saturday, a crowd had formed at the main entrance as the doors re-opened to the first visitors of the day on schedule at 09:30 am (4.30pm Singapore time).</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"I''m quite worried about coming today, but as we weren''t able to visit yesterday we decided to come back anyway," 28-year-old Russian visitor Elena Lordugen told AFP.</p>\r\n<div id="innity-in-post" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Soldiers in uniform with machine guns could be seen patrolling as usual, with routine bag checks also undertaken by Louvre security staff.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Ali Tali, a Turkish tourist in his 40s, shrugged off their presence. "We''re used these security measures in Turkey," he said.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">French investigators say Friday''s attacker, in a black T-shirt bearing a skull design and armed with two machetes, lunged at four patrolling French soldiers while shouting "Allahu Akbar" ("God is greatest").</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">They are examining the Twitter account of an Egyptian man named Abdallah El Hamahmy after around a dozen messages were posted in Arabic between 9:27-9:34 am (4.27pm to 4.34pm Singapore time), just minutes prior to the attack.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"In the name of Allah... for our brothers in Syria and fighters across the world," El Hamahmy wrote, before making reference to the Islamic State jihadist group in another tweet a minute later.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">One of the troops was "lightly injured" in the attack after being struck on the head in a public area that leads to one of the museum''s entrance.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">A second soldier opened fire five times and hit the machete-wielder in the stomach.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"The attacker fell to the ground, seriously wounded," Paris prosecutor Francois Molins told a press conference late Friday.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">His condition stabilised overnight in a Parisian hospital, a source close to the case told AFP.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Based on his phone and visa records, he is thought to be a 29-year-old Egyptian national who is resident in the United Arab Emirates.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Investigators have established he entered France legally on a flight from Dubai on January 26 and had rented an expensive apartment near the Champs Elysee, sources close to the case told AFP.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The government of the United Arab Emirates, which includes Dubai, condemned the "hateful crime" and assured France of its "full solidarity".</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">President Francois Hollande said that "there is little doubt as to the terrorist nature of this act," an assessment echoed by Prime Minister Bernard Cazeneuve.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">France was already reeling from a string of terror attacks over the last two years and the country has been under a state of emergency since November 2015.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The economy, immigration and security are major issues for voters ahead of this year''s presidential and parliamentary elections forecast to confirm the country''s shift to the right after five years of Socialist rule.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">US President Donald Trump tweeted that a "new radical Islamic terrorist has just attacked in Louvre Museum in Paris. Tourists were locked down. France on edge again. GET SMART US." Witnesses described scenes of panic as people fled the Louvre complex following the incident.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">"We heard gunshots. We didn''t know what it was about. Then we evacuated the employees and we left," one man who works in a nearby restaurant told AFP.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The Louvre, a former palace in the heart of the city, has seen annual visitor numbers fall by some two million since 2015 to 7.3 million.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">The series of terror attacks in France began in January 2015 when jihadist gunmen rampaged through the offices of the Charlie Hebdo satirical newspaper and a Jewish supermarket in Paris, leaving 17 people dead in three days of bloodshed.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">Ten months later, gunmen and suicide bombers from the Islamic State jihadist group attacked bars, restaurants, a concert hall and the national stadium in Paris, killing 130 people.</p>\r\n<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding-right: 50px; color: #333333; font-family: SelaneTen, Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">And last July, a Tunisian extremist rammed a lorry through crowds celebrating Bastille Day in Nice on France''s south coast, crushing 86 people to death.</p>', 'louvre,tourist', 'How Tos', 'assets/images/louvre.PNG', 'saroj', '2017-01-26', 393, 998, NULL);

